var personObj = {"name":"john", "age":30, "married":false}

<parameter name = "name", value = "john"/>
<parameter name = "age", value = 30/>
<parameter name = "married", value = false/>

Request : HTTP Methods, Request Payload / body, Request Headers (Authorization - basic / bearer / token), Params (Path, Query)

Response : HTTP Response Status Code, Response Headers, Response body / payload

HTTP Response Codes:
 - Successful - 2**, 201 (Created), 200 (Success), 204 (No Content)
 - Redirection - 3**, 309
 - Client side error - 4**, 404 Not Found, 401 Authentication failed, 403 unauthorized
 - Server side error - 5**, 500 Internal server error, 500 NPE


URL - https://petstore.swagger.io/v2/pet/23/uploadImage
Base URI + Resource / Endpoint = URL
Base URI - https://petstore.swagger.io/v2
Endpoint/Resource Locator - 
pet endpoint : /pet/23/uploadImage
store endpoint : /store/order

Path param - only pass the value throug url
Query Param - after ? or & key = value. Both will be passed



